---
Title: "My-first-week-at-GitHub"
Date: 2026-04-09
---
First week at GitHub has been a slower than expected ramp up, but a lot of self-guided development and exercises. 
I've appreciated the onboarding approach of GitHub which focuses more on Culture, Environment, and teams.
I'd love for there to be some more hands-on focus and guidance around Product Learning and Development (but maybe I'm just impatient)
The only prickly part has been that GitHub recently fulled merged into the broader Microsoft ecosystem so some of the docs don't align correctly internally and permissions are sometimes not fully integrated on day1
